summary:
The Security Council,
Welcoming the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations operation in Cyprus, 
Reaffirms all its relevant resolutions on Cyprus, in particular resolution 1251 (1999) and subsequent resolutions;
Decides to extend the mandate of UNFICYP until 15 December 2004;
 Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to lift all remaining restrictions on UNFICYP and restore the military status quo in Strovilia as of 30 June 2000;
 Requests the Secretary-General to report on the implementation of this resolution; 
Decides to remain seized of the matter; 
 Welcoming the Secretary-General's intention to review UNFICYP's mandate, force levels and concept of operation within three months.
